1
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:21,980
Joe, that's why your parents
told you not to jump on the bed!

2
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:25,400
The One With the Jam

3
00:01:12,364 --> 00:01:15,575
Hey, look at me!
I'm making jam!

4
00:01:15,825 --> 00:01:19,913
- I've been at it since 4 a.m.
- Where'd you get fruit at 4 a.m.?

5
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:23,583
Down at the docks.
You know, you can get it wholesale.

6
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:27,170
I didn't know there were docks.

7
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:30,757
Is it broken?

8
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:33,593
No, but I gotta wear this
for a couple weeks.

9
00:01:33,843 --> 00:01:37,389
You tell the doctor you did it
jumping on your bed?

10
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:40,934
No. I had a whole story
worked out, but then...

11
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:42,519
...Chandler sold me out.

12
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:48,400
I didn't think the doctor would buy
that it "fell out of the socket".

13
00:01:49,317 --> 00:01:53,113
What is this? Fruit?

14
00:01:54,864 --> 00:01:56,449
Monica's making jam.

15
00:01:56,700 --> 00:02:01,121
Jam? I love jam! How come
we never have jam at our place?

16
00:02:01,371 --> 00:02:04,582
Because the kids need new shoes.

17
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:08,628
I'm going into business. I'm sick of
being depressed about Richard.

18
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:11,506
I needed a plan.
A plan to get over my man.

19
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:16,344
What's the opposite of man? Jam!

20
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:20,598
Joey, don't! It's way too hot!

21
00:02:26,104 --> 00:02:29,649
This'll just be my batch.

22
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,083
That's it.

23
00:02:47,334 --> 00:02:48,793
Hey, you, J. Crew guy...

24
00:02:49,044 --> 00:02:50,795
Why are you following me?

25
00:02:51,046 --> 00:02:53,590
All week, everywhere I look,
there's you.

26
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:57,093
You wouldn't return my calls.
You sent back my letters.

27
00:02:57,344 --> 00:03:01,097
One more chance, Ursula. Please.

28
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:05,894
This is awkward.

29
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:11,316
Yeah, because you want Ursula,
and I'm Phoebe. Twin sisters.

30
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:14,235
Seriously.

31
00:03:14,486 --> 00:03:16,863
That's great.
I'm stalking the wrong woman.

32
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:19,574
I am such a dingus!

33
00:03:19,824 --> 00:03:21,743
Oh, you're not a dingus.

34
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:25,663
I just want you to know
I wasn't always like this.

35
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:31,878
Before I met your sister, I was a
normal guy who sold cellular phones.

36
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:34,923
Look, it's not your fault.

37
00:03:35,173 --> 00:03:40,345
I mean, this is just
what she does to guys, okay?

38
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:42,013
Well, thanks.

39
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:45,141
Wait. I got a little story.

40
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:49,270
Once, in junior high school,
I thought I was a witch.

41
00:03:49,521 --> 00:03:53,900
And a guidance counselor told me
something that might help you.

42
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:59,030
He said, "Okay, you're not a witch.
You're just an average student."

43
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:03,326
- See what I'm saying?
- Not really.

44
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:06,287
Well, get over it.

45
00:04:07,622 --> 00:04:12,127
You seem like a really nice guy.

46
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:14,504
Don't be so hard on yourself, okay?

47
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:20,468
You're right. I know you're right.
And thanks for being so nice.

48
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:23,763
Thanks a lot.

49
00:04:24,014 --> 00:04:27,017
Want to get some coffee?

50
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:34,607
You don't have to
walk behind me anymore.

51
00:04:38,737 --> 00:04:43,700
"Gone for more jars. Be back later.
Monica Geller."

52
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:47,203
Wait a minute. Look!

53
00:04:47,495 --> 00:04:49,748
It's an empty apartment.

54
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:53,918
We're all alone
in an empty apartment.

55
00:04:54,169 --> 00:04:57,213
I have to be at work
in 10 minutes.

56
00:04:57,464 --> 00:05:03,178
All right. It's not like
I'm employee of the year or anything.

57
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:08,016
There it is!

58
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:11,770
Oh, that's what you mean.

59
00:05:13,271 --> 00:05:14,856
Do I look fat?

60
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:17,317
No.

61
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:18,610
I accept that.

62
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:24,199
When Janice asked me and I said no,
she thought I was calling her a cow.

63
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:27,660
Walk us through it, honey.
Walk us through it.

64
00:05:27,911 --> 00:05:34,292
Janice said, "Hi. Do I look fat
today?" And I looked at her...

65
00:05:34,542 --> 00:05:37,754
You looked at her?

66
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:41,174
You never look.

67
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:47,180
You just answer. It's like a reflex.
"Do I look fat?" "No."

68
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:51,935
"Is she prettier than I am?"
"No."

69
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:53,520
"Does size matter?"

70
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:56,731
And it works both ways.

71
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:01,486
So you both just
know this stuff?

72
00:06:01,736 --> 00:06:06,324
After 30 or 40 fights,
you kind of catch on.

73
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:08,368
Okay. For instance:

74
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:12,831
Janice is coming back from a trip.
She gives you two options.

75
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:16,292
Option one: She'll take a cab
home from the airport.

76
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:20,088
Option two: You can meet her
at baggage claim. What do you do?

77
00:06:20,338 --> 00:06:21,381
Easy. Baggage claim.

78
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:25,010
Wrong! Now you're single.

79
00:06:25,969 --> 00:06:29,139
It's actually secret
option number three.

80
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:33,560
You meet her at the gate. That way
she knows you love her.

81
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:35,145
Okay, this is good.

82
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:38,940
All right, I have one.
Janice likes to cuddle...

83
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,693
...at night,
which I'm all for.

84
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:45,739
But when you want to go to sleep,
you want some space.

85
00:06:45,989 --> 00:06:48,491
So how do I tell her that without...

86
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:52,120
...you know, accidentally
calling her fat or something?

87
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:57,917
Sorry, honey. We can't help you
there, because we're cuddly sleepers.

88
00:06:58,168 --> 00:06:59,753
I'm late for work.

89
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:03,506
- Are you guys coming down?
- Yeah. I'm right behind you.

90
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:07,177
Good luck, Chandler.

91
00:07:09,471 --> 00:07:12,432
The sleeping thing.

92
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:15,226
Very tricky business,
but solvable.

93
00:07:15,477 --> 00:07:19,731
I thought you were "cuddly sleepers".

94
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:23,151
No, not cuddly.
Not me. Just her.

95
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:25,528
I'm like you.
I need the room.

96
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:28,615
Okay, come here.

97
00:07:31,034 --> 00:07:34,454
Okay. You're in bed.

98
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:41,628
I'll use the cushion.

99
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:45,674
Okay. You're in bed.
She's over on your side, cuddling.

100
00:07:45,924 --> 00:07:49,135
Now, you wait for her to drift off...

101
00:07:49,386 --> 00:07:51,805
...and then you hug her...

102
00:07:52,055 --> 00:07:56,726
...and roll her over
to her side of the bed.

103
00:07:56,976 --> 00:07:59,729
And then you...

104
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:03,566
...roll away.

105
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:07,153
Hug for her.

106
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:12,409
Roll for you.

107
00:08:12,534 --> 00:08:14,411
The old "hug and roll".

108
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:19,708
One question. You're pretending
the pillow's a girl, right?

109
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:26,006
Remember when you were a kid, your
mom would send you to the movies...

110
00:08:26,256 --> 00:08:30,427
...with a jar of jam
and a little spoon?

111
00:08:32,262 --> 00:08:35,432
You're so pretty.

112
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:44,941
You know that guy who's been
following me? I talked to him today.

113
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:49,320
You talked to him?
Are you crazy?

114
00:08:49,863 --> 00:08:54,701
First, I'm not crazy.
And second, say it, don't spray it.

115
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:58,371
Anyway, his name is Malcolm,
and he wasn't following me.

116
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:02,959
I mean, he was,
but he thought I was Ursula.

117
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:08,048
That's why he couldn't just
come up and talk to me.

118
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:12,510
Because of the restraining order.

119
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:16,848
Not feeling better about Malcolm.

120
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:19,059
No, no, he's not a kook.

121
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:23,313
He's just this very passionate,
incredibly romantic guy...

122
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:26,441
...that just got
a teensy bit carried away.

123
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:30,195
We get along really well,
and he's so cute.

124
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:35,575
Oh, my God! You've got a crush
on your sister's stalker.

125
00:09:35,825 --> 00:09:38,703
I'm going to help him get
"de-Ursula-ized".

126
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:41,998
Like I did for Joey
after he went out with her.

127
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:44,376
I didn't stalk her.

128
00:09:44,626 --> 00:09:48,755
I asked for the news,
not the weather.

129
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:56,429
Joey, this is for you.
It's blackberry currant.

130
00:10:01,768 --> 00:10:03,353
Joe, I got to ask.

131
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:07,232
The girl from the xero x place,
buck naked...

132
00:10:07,482 --> 00:10:11,194
...or a big tub of jam?

133
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:14,739
Put your hands together.

134
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:20,412
Take your time with that.
It's my last batch.

135
00:10:20,662 --> 00:10:22,956
No more jam?

136
00:10:23,206 --> 00:10:25,250
What happened to
your jam plan?

137
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:29,004
I figured out I'd need to charge
$ 17 a jar just to break even.

138
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:33,508
So I've got a new plan now.
Babies.

139
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:37,762
Well, you'll need
much bigger jars.

140
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:41,891
- What are you talking about?
- About me having a baby.

141
00:10:42,142 --> 00:10:44,394
- Are you serious?
- Yeah.

142
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:47,856
The jam plan helped me
take control of my life.

143
00:10:48,106 --> 00:10:50,984
So I thought, "What is
the most important thing to me?"

144
00:10:51,234 --> 00:10:54,154
And that's when I came up
with the baby plan.

145
00:10:54,404 --> 00:10:57,157
Aren't you forgetting something?

146
00:10:57,407 --> 00:11:01,703
What is that guy's name?
Dad!

147
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:05,582
It took me 28 years to find a man
I wanted to spend my life with.

148
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:09,878
If I have to wait another 28 years,
I'll be 56 before I can have a baby.

149
00:11:10,128 --> 00:11:13,173
And that's just stupid.

150
00:11:13,423 --> 00:11:16,843
That's what's stupid?

151
00:11:17,427 --> 00:11:23,099
I don't need an actual man.
Just a few of his best swimmers.

152
00:11:23,183 --> 00:11:26,353
And there are places
you can go to get that... stuff.

153
00:11:26,603 --> 00:11:30,190
Down to the docks again?

154
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:42,911
Night-night, Bing-a-ling.

155
00:11:43,078 --> 00:11:45,288
Night-night...

156
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:48,291
...Janice.

157
00:11:50,877 --> 00:11:53,338
{y:i}Look at all the room on her side!

158
00:11:53,588 --> 00:11:57,217
{y:i}A giant penguin
{y:i}could fit over there.

159
00:11:57,884 --> 00:12:00,762
{y:i}That'd be weird, though.

160
00:12:01,096 --> 00:12:02,430
{y:i}Hug and roll time.

161
00:12:02,681 --> 00:12:04,974
{y:i}I'm hugging. I'm hugging.

162
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:07,977
{y:i}You're rolling, and...

163
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:10,313
{y:i}Yes! Freedom!

164
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,899
{y:i}Except for this arm!

165
00:12:13,149 --> 00:12:16,986
{y:i}I'm stuck. Stuck arm.

166
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:20,365
{y:i}Time for the old tablecloth trick.
{y:i}One fluid motion.

167
00:12:20,615 --> 00:12:22,283
{y:i}Quick like a cat.

168
00:12:22,534 --> 00:12:25,495
{y:i}And one, two...

169
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:28,498
{y:i}... three!

170
00:12:34,462 --> 00:12:36,214
Here's my binoculars.

171
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:39,050
Oh, great.
You're doing great.

172
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:42,387
Going strong. Keep going.

173
00:12:42,637 --> 00:12:45,390
These are my night-vision goggles.

174
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:50,061
This is the book I pretend to read
when I'm watching her in the park.

175
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:55,358
And these are "Madlibs".
They're just for fun.

176
00:12:56,192 --> 00:13:00,655
This is the log I kept,
recording her every movement.

177
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:02,532
Want to hear some of it?

178
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:05,744
Not even a little bit.

179
00:13:05,994 --> 00:13:07,037
It's about you.

180
00:13:07,287 --> 00:13:10,498
Okay then.

181
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:16,212
"I met Phoebe today."

182
00:13:16,463 --> 00:13:20,592
"She was really nice to me
even though I'm such a loser."

183
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:23,803
"And when I was walking home,
I thought about her a lot."

184
00:13:24,054 --> 00:13:27,974
"It was weird, but kind of cool."

185
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,477
Good.

186
00:13:30,727 --> 00:13:33,563
So what were you thinking?

187
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:36,399
I was thinking what it'd be
like to kiss you.

188
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:39,569
- Really?
- No.

189
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:45,158
That's just something I said now
so that maybe I could kiss you.

190
00:13:45,408 --> 00:13:48,203
Oh, okay.

191
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:57,379
No, it's all right.
I just had a jar of mustard.

192
00:13:57,420 --> 00:14:03,385
Okay. Sperm donor number 03815,
come on down!

193
00:14:03,635 --> 00:14:05,428
Okay, he's 6'2", 170 pounds.

194
00:14:05,679 --> 00:14:08,765
He describes himself
as a male Gina Davis.

195
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:12,519
You mean there's
more than one of us?

196
00:14:12,852 --> 00:14:16,106
You can't do this, Mon.
If you do this, I'll...

197
00:14:16,356 --> 00:14:19,776
- You'll what?
- I'll tell Mom.

198
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:23,822
I'm sorry, but he's right.
I love you, but you're crazy.

199
00:14:24,072 --> 00:14:26,783
Why? Why is this crazy?

200
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:29,577
- So this isn't the ideal way...
- Oh, it's not...

201
00:14:29,828 --> 00:14:32,622
Lips moving. Still talking.

202
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,916
It may not be ideal, but...

203
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:37,293
...I'm so ready.

204
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:40,046
I see the way
Ben looks at you.

205
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,924
It makes me ache, you know?

206
00:14:43,174 --> 00:14:46,636
Check it out! Jam crackers!

207
00:14:49,431 --> 00:14:51,599
Okay. All right, how's this?

208
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:54,644
Twenty-seven, Italian-American guy.

209
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:56,521
He's an actor.

210
00:14:56,771 --> 00:14:58,440
Born in Queens.

211
00:14:58,690 --> 00:15:02,569
Wow! Big family.
Seven sisters...

212
00:15:02,819 --> 00:15:06,489
...and he's the only... boy.

213
00:15:09,284 --> 00:15:12,829
Oh, my God! Under personal comments:
"New York Knicks rule."

214
00:15:13,079 --> 00:15:16,166
Yeah, the Knicks rule!

215
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:20,879
Joey, this is you!

216
00:15:21,129 --> 00:15:23,965
Let me see.

217
00:15:24,883 --> 00:15:27,093
Oh, right!

218
00:15:27,344 --> 00:15:29,054
You went to a sperm bank?

219
00:15:29,304 --> 00:15:32,057
Right after I did that
sex study at NYU.

220
00:15:32,307 --> 00:15:34,851
Remember that sweater I gave you?

221
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:38,063
That's how you bought it?

222
00:15:38,313 --> 00:15:42,901
No. That's what I was wearing
when I donated.

223
00:15:44,611 --> 00:15:48,114
I'm surprised there's any
of my boys left.

224
00:15:48,365 --> 00:15:52,285
It is pretty competitive. There's
an actual rocket scientist here.

225
00:15:52,535 --> 00:15:56,831
Maybe I should have them put my
"Days of our Lives" gig on here.

226
00:15:57,082 --> 00:16:00,335
Juice this up a little.

227
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:04,047
How's the maniac?

228
00:16:04,297 --> 00:16:07,967
He's yummy.
We did a little kissing.

229
00:16:08,218 --> 00:16:10,095
Phoebe, what are you doing?

230
00:16:10,345 --> 00:16:15,517
No, no. He's not into that anymore.
He quit for me.

231
00:16:15,767 --> 00:16:20,146
This guy has been obsessed with
your sister for God knows how long.

232
00:16:20,397 --> 00:16:23,274
You don't just give that up.

233
00:16:23,525 --> 00:16:27,404
He gave me his night-vision
goggles and everything.

234
00:16:27,654 --> 00:16:31,616
You're taking the word of a guy
who has night-vision goggles?

235
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:35,662
He's not still following her.
You think he's still following her?

236
00:16:35,912 --> 00:16:40,500
Wake up and smell
the restraining order.

237
00:16:40,917 --> 00:16:42,210
What should I do?

238
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:45,463
If you really like this guy,
you should just trust him.

239
00:16:45,714 --> 00:16:47,549
Thank you, Monica.

240
00:16:47,799 --> 00:16:49,676
Or you could follow him.

241
00:16:49,926 --> 00:16:53,638
That's what I'd do.
Forget mine.

242
00:16:55,724 --> 00:16:56,975
What happened?

243
00:16:57,225 --> 00:16:59,519
Crazy Chandler spun me...

244
00:16:59,769 --> 00:17:01,438
...off the bed.

245
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:05,942
Wow! Spinning!
Sounds like fun.

246
